Name:Conditional

Categories: Language

Related:

Synopsis:
* Syntax: `$Exp_1$ ? $Exp_2$ : $Exp_3$`
* Type:


| `$Exp_1$`   | `$Exp_2$`  |  `$Exp_3$` | Result   |
|:----------|:----------|:----------|-------|
|   `bool`       | `int`           |  `int`            | `int`   |
|  `bool`       | `int`           |  `real`          | `real`  |
|  `bool`       | `real`         |  `real`          | `real`  |

Description: If the value of $Exp$ is `true` then the value of $Exp_1$ else the value of $Exp_2$.

Examples:
<screen>
(3 > 2) ? 10 : 20
(3 > 20) ? 10 : 20
</screen>

